HEADWORD: Cast-off
<hw>Cast"-off`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Cast or laid aside;
thrown away; discarded; <as>as, <ex>cast-off</ex>
clothes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> discarded, junked, scrap(prenominal),
waste.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

